review_text: Beautiful beach and very long so it is ideal for long walks. On both sides of the beach there are saltwater pools. Pay attention to the signs as there are dangerous currents and it is always full of Portuguese man o' war jellyfish.
Beautiful beach and great sunset views, and if you are lucky you can spot whales during mating season, endless views of the ocean.

review_title: Beautiful beach, lagoon, walks and rock pool
review_text: Narrabeen beach has so much to offer. Including exposed rocks during low tide, a lagoon that is located next to the rock pool. Long sandy beach to go on a nice long walk or bi-centennial coastal walk up the coast to Warriewood beach and further.

North Narrabeen has long been renowned for having some of the best, most consistent waves on the East Coast and along the way the area has produced some of Australia's most famous surfers. From the lookout on the point at the northern end of the beach you can see the current crop ply their skills. (Just look for the crowd of onlookers with cameras.)
If you are not a red-hot surfer North Narrabeen still has plenty to offer. There are very good ocean baths also at the north end that attract families and serious lap swimmers. The beach is also very long, extending several kms to Collaroy Beach in the south. Very good for a long beach walk and there are plenty of uncrowded (though also unpatrolled) sections along the way too.

North Narrabeen beach is nestled bedside Narrabeen lagoon and has a stunning Rockpool and a long sandy beach which is fabulous for surfing .

Walking around the lagoon is also excellent for all age groups with a dedicated pathway for bicycles and pedestrians. The lagoon also has several beautiful spots for swimming, fishing or canoeing ?.

North Narrabeen beach is located on the northern beaches 25km north of the CBD.
Swimming in our oceans with life guards and on North Narrabeen is a gr888t day out at the beach for anyone
Absolutely beautiful spot. Love the ocean rockpool, which is excellent for recreational or lap swimming. The headland and inlet are fantastic

review_title: Beautiful Beach for walking or Surfing
review_text: Fabulous beach, with excellent waves for surfing. Clean and picturesque.  Has a great rock pool for swimming as well, and the lagoon, but this needs to be open to the surf, for optimum water quality.

review_title: North Narrabeen Surf Life Saving Club. Has a hideaway cafe/restaurant, that is not mentioned in Trip Adviser.
review_text: With “eat in or alfresco” on the balcony overlooking the surf & sand. My daughters & I had a delicious meal, and great coffee. It is so good we often eat there, . Prices reasonable. Casual dress. So relaxing watching the waves roll in! Hidden gem!
A very nice beach, wasn't busy when we were there but we were told by locals that it does get very busy in Summer. Most public car parking is paid parking and actively monitored by Council.
Maybe I shouldn't tell people as I love this place. Great for taking photos at sunrise or sunset, as you can see both East and West. You can swim in the surf or in the rock pool.
great beach, was very quiet when I went there, we had a great time. it's a sandy beach with great sunset view

North Narrabeen Rockpool: this is an ocean pool on a point so it has a good view on three sides. The path from the car park is flat and not too long. The pool bottom is sandy and it has a nice wooden boardwalk where you can leave your stuff. Would be better at high tide with waves crashing all around.
Like all the Northern Beaches crashing waves and sand. Make sure you swim between the flags there can be a significant sweep.

review_title: One of the best beaches in Sydney
review_text: I grew up around here and love this beach, go there most weekends in Summer for a walk and/or a swim

A beautiful patrolled beach on the Northern Beaches of Sydney. Glorious rockpool for pottering and looking at the lcoal rock life plus for the kids the opening of the Lagoon comes in from the sea and there is a wonderfully safe and clean Lagoon area to swim. Plenty of Cafes are close by and the North Narrabeen Surf Club has a functioning Bar Friday, Saturday and Sunday afternoon/evenings where you can sit on the balcony overlooking the azure beachfront and enjoy a cold one or two. PARADISE!
Love Nth Narrabeen. Never over the top busy with people and huge beach area. Add to that the lake and pool at the northern end and you can’t ask for more.

Enjoy your time at the beach & then enjoy great coffee & food at the local cafe opposite the beach.

Great for an early walk & dip in the ocean.

Great surf spot.  Swell magnetic.  Orangish sand.  Very localised / heavy crew. Intermediate level wave.  Don't bother surfing here unless you're experienced and an expert.  Others won't get waves. Body boarders sre not made welcome. Surfing royalty are out in the line up most good days

review_title: Narrabeen - Not a good place to visit
review_text: An very undeveloped area. Internet is still ADSL1 which is very out-of-dated (even using Telstra network). You will find it hard to surf the internet sometimes. Limited shops and cafe, nothing much to do except the beach. Foods in Narrabeen are terrible. Not recommend unless you grew up from bush.
What a fabulous beach with a lake as well (great for younger children). There is surf patrol too so it is safe if you want to go body surfing (or surfing).

review_title: Great lunch and very good coffee
review_text:
Been here a couple of times , sometimes for a coffee , or breakfast and others for lunch .

Very friendly team , fresh ingredients, and again great coffee . Location is also one of the nicest hangouts on North Narrabeen

A slice of heaven on the northern beaches.
The beach is great for surfing with a right to left break from the point.
the beach can be a bit rough for swimming but the lagoon that can be accessed from the road or the beach is just perfict
This place is superb all year long. It is more than just a summer destination, and a lot of walking all over the place. The surf can get hectic sometimes so beware. And enjoy!!

One of the longest beaches in Sydney, North Narrabeen is a great place to visit. The Northern End has cafes, is near the caravan park and has a beach pool. It can get rough at times but the lagoon just behind the dunes is a great place for young families when the water mouth is open to the sea. Remember to always swim between the flags.
What more can you say about the best beach on earth. when the lake is open and the sun is out where else would you rather be.

Good sea water pool if the sea is too rough or you just want a leisurely swim, but a great beach for surfing or just diving through the waves. Good loo with changing facilities, car park about 150 yds from pool, with small cafe nearby. Life guards on duty with flagged areas most of the time, never seen it too busy.

North Narrabeen Narabeen is a great beach , can stroll along the sand there is a park and playground at one end and the rock pool and park at the other
If you are a surfer it looks good , certainly good for a swim but like all the Northern Beaches swim in the flags and ask the locals for advice on where is best to swim
Quite a few cafes close to the beach
Just a good beach for lots of activities , parking around the area is both metered and free

Narrabeen beach offers you three places in one. If you have some small children with you, the Narrabeen lagoon or the rock pool is for you. If you’re a surfer or just prefer the ocean, go to the beach. All the three of them are next to each other.
